An 8-inch by 8-inch square is folded along a diagonal creating a triangular region. This resulting triangular region is then folded so that the right angle vertex just meets the midpoint of the hypotenuse. What is the area of the resulting trapezoidal figure in square inches?

[asy]
fill((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,10)--(0,10)--cycle,gray(.7));
draw((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,10)--(0,10)--cycle,linewidth(1));
fill((20,0)--(20,10)--(30,10)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((20,0)--(20,10)--(30,10)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((20,0)--(30,0)--(30,10),dashed);
fill((40,0)--(40,5)--(45,10)--(50,10)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((40,0)--(40,5)--(45,10)--(50,10)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((40,5)--(45,5)--(45,10));
draw((40,5)--(40,10)--(45,10),dashed);
draw((40,0)--(50,0)--(50,10),dashed);
draw((12,5)--(18,5),Arrow);
draw((32,5)--(38,5),Arrow);

[/asy]

inference:
The diagonal of the square is $8\sqrt{2}$ inches long.  When the square is folded along the diagonal, the hypotenuse of the triangular region is $8\sqrt{2}$ inches long.  The midpoint of the hypotenuse is $4\sqrt{2}$ inches from each vertex.

[asy]
fill((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,10)--(0,10)--cycle,gray(.7));
draw((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,10)--(0,10)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((0,0)--(10,10),linewidth(1));
draw((0,0)--(5,5)--(10,10),dashed);
draw((0,0)--(10,0)--(10,5)--(5,5),dashed);
label("$8\sqrt{2}$",(5,5)--(10,10),SE);
label("$4\sqrt{2}$",(5,5)--(10,10),NE);
[/asy]

Folding the triangular region so that the right angle vertex meets the midpoint of the hypotenuse creates a trapezoid.  The base of the trapezoid is the hypotenuse of the original triangular region, which is $8\sqrt{2}$ inches long.  The height of the trapezoid is the distance from the midpoint of the hypotenuse to the original right angle vertex, which is $4\sqrt{2}$ inches.  The length of the other base of the trapezoid is equal to the length of the altitude of the original triangle.  This altitude is also the shorter leg of the right triangle formed by the diagonal of the square.  The legs of this triangle are $8$ inches and $8$ inches, so the altitude is $8$ inches.

[asy]
fill((40,0)--(40,5)--(45,10)--(50,10)--cycle,gray(0.7));
draw((40,0)--(40,5)--(45,10)--(50,10)--cycle,linewidth(1));
draw((40,5)--(45,5)--(45,10));
draw((40,5)--(40,10)--(45,10),dashed);
draw((40,0)--(50,0)--(50,10),dashed);
label("$8\sqrt{2}$",(40,0)--(50,0),S);
label("$4\sqrt{2}$",(40,0)--(40,5),W);
label("$8$",(40,0)--(40,5),NE);
[/asy]

The area of the trapezoid is $\frac{1}{2}(8\sqrt{2} + 8)(4\sqrt{2}) = \boxed{64}$ square inches.

